{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/2017/10/03/learn-python-iteration-for-loop-while-loop/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Gatsby Advanced Blog","author":"Nikhil Gohil","homepage":"https://nikhilgohil11.com"}},"post":{"id":"7fc53569-662e-5d9f-9f88-d45e621e5322","html":"<p>In my previous post <a href=\"https://nikhilgohil11.com/2017/10/03/learn-python-variable/\">variables</a> and <a href=\"https://nikhilgohil11.com/2017/10/03/learn-python-conditional-statement-if-if-else/\">conditional statement</a> covered.\nNow let’s see Iteration (for loop, while loop)\nSo many ways I can use for loop\nI can iterate through string like this</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"hljs-python\"><code class=\"hljs-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> character <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span> “Nikhil”<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n     <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span> character</code></pre></div>\n<p>Output:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"op\"><pre class=\"hljs-op\"><code class=\"hljs-op\">N\ni\nk\nh\ni\nl</code></pre></div>\n<p>Also, I can iterate through an array</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"hljs-python\"><code class=\"hljs-python\">numbers <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">6</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">7</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">8</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">9</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> number <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span> numbers<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n     <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span> number</code></pre></div>\n<p>Output:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"op\"><pre class=\"hljs-op\"><code class=\"hljs-op\">1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n6\n7\n8\n9\n0</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now suppose I want to iterate between range from 4 to 11, then in python its very easy</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"hljs-python\"><code class=\"hljs-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> number <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">range</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">11</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n     <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span> number</code></pre></div>\n<p>Output:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"op\"><pre class=\"hljs-op\"><code class=\"hljs-op\">4\n5\n6\n7\n8\n9\n10\n11</code></pre></div>\n<p>Hmm.. this is really cool. Let’s look at while</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"hljs-python\"><code class=\"hljs-python\">number <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">4</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">while</span> number <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;=</span><span class=\"token number\">11</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span> number\n number <span class=\"token operator\">+=</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Output:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"op\"><pre class=\"hljs-op\"><code class=\"hljs-op\">4\n5\n6\n7\n8\n9\n10\n11</code></pre></div>\n<p>I am trying while with boolean. Yes its simple and expected</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"hljs-python\"><code class=\"hljs-python\">student_passed <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> true\n<span class=\"token keyword\">while</span> student_passed<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>“Congratulations!!!”<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p> Output:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"op\"><pre class=\"hljs-op\"><code class=\"hljs-op\">Congratulations!!!</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Learn Python — Iteration (for loop, while loop)","path":"/2017/10/03/learn-python-iteration-for-loop-while-loop/","images":["images/post3/post3.jpg"],"category":"Python","tags":["Python","Learning"],"date":"2017-10-05T00:00:00.000Z","components":null,"tweets":null,"summary":"In my previous post variables and conditional statement covered. Now let’s see Iteration (for loop, while loop) So many ways I can use for loop..."}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false}}}